messages.text: Is this the Rhys Lakes University "Scohlarship Line?"
Sorry, I know that sounds weird.
I was told to text this number at 3:15pm with my essay reponse.
my name is dr. kline, "head of admissions"
Oh sorry. Emily Tyler. Nice to meet you!
emily: real quick....you don't have to write these messages with perfect punctuation and capitalization
I've never done something like this before.
i want to read the real you
I can do that, I'm just really netvous
you must be following the instructions in our new catalog
which means the essay question on the table must be: "How will your education at our University make a difference for society?"
First, let me discuss the main issue I am focusing on. In my opinion, our most important issue as a society is the struggle to come to terms with diminishing global resources.
that's nice and all but is it really what you wanted to say
and say the "right" things and jump through the "right" hoops
we're not looking for a trained show dog
Uhhh Like, really stand up? For real?
yes for real. don't waste my time and i won't waste yours...not a sec to waste
if you're at the address I think you are, i want you to look out that small window on the far right side of your house that's facing the street
No no I mean yes that's my address but what are you doing?
look out the window and youll see a woman in a black dress across the street
Are you messing w me? don’t particularly like pranks
you're the one that texted us, does our school seem like a prank to you
i always heard freaky rumors about your school
we do things a little differently, but that's what it takes to be on the cutting edge
Jesus, yes. I do. What do you want
emily. this is where I'm putting you to the test a little...you need to go with me on this journey, okay
you play along or you can fucking forget it
i don't think you're thinking clearly, don't think you want to "f this"
uhhh why am i putting up with this? why wouldn't I just go somewhere else
RLU offers an unsurpassable program for an individual like you
You know this to be true
if you do as i say, dearest emily, and you PASS this...examination...you get in free
why should I believe you? I don't even know you
and i’m a lil suspicious of these overly “ominous” messages
i can give you the names of about ten other places that'll eat your PLAIN VANILLA RESPONSE right up
YOU called at your appointment time
YOU are looking at the woman i said would be there
it's not up to me, the head of admissions, to prove to you, Random Emily, that im "creditable"
Ok...so I'm looking at this woman, so now what?
Do I need to bring anything?
i want you to grab a roll of tape
and grab whatever's the first knife you see in the kitchen
Ok nm this is not for me
OK I'm going to the kitchen
she can't see you have it
if you show any sign of fear it's over
cross the street and go talk to her
Crossing the street to the lying lady
tell her you have something for her
she can't speak, she has paper and she will write down what she has to tell you
I don't know if I can make it out...
The way she looks at me
But this looks like a map
there are a bunch of arrows
even in most lies theres some kernel of truth
Well I recognize this square of benches i think
And she drew a bunch of trees, one of them...
It looks like a knife's sticking out of it
The arrows are all wrong though
she thinks she knows people like you but she’s wrong about you
Well I know these benches and trees
It's in the little park right by here
I can almost see it from here, but there's mist everywhere
txt me when you get there
The fog is hanging over everything
Like it wants to swallow me up
the tree she drew is the tree I always used to climb
when I’d play in this park with my grandpa
How would you know he’s passed
anyway, pretty sure this tree never had a door painted on it before
if it looks like a door
well then make it a door
Theres no more wood inside, only darkness
emily, you should not feel obligated to continue this examination
I can make decisions for myself
tbh it was always the normal world that felt crazy to me
at least I have a purpose right now
just it’s important to mentally prepare you for the unpleasantness ahead
this world as you believe you know it is about to become stranger than youd ever imagine
I like you dr., with your vaguely threatening msgs
ok before you go into the tunnel
you're going to have to feel along the walls
down into the stomach of the passages below
but i tell you now you must keep your phone off
it must be off until the room with the red candle
you will hear them snuffling about in the dark
if they see the light they will catch you and it's over
and don't tell me stuff like that
Anyway the candle, there's these bits of rolled up paper on the table
I think it's another map, but they won't stay flat
But I have the tape so I'm gonna use that
It's a map of...sounds I guess?
I've never seen anything like it
"For Those Who Are More Than More" it says, then it’s arrows to words and words to arrows to...sounds
I’ll let you know when I get to each word, ok
The “drip drip” it leads to a river
the river leads to these grinding stones, which
Where is whistling wind coming from so far down? anyway
This flame, I'm looking at it but it sounds like no fire I've ever seen
I don't know what's making this rustling
Or this gloppy flapping above me
I hear the “echoing” voices, sounds like humming
Sounds like the center of the earth
The sounds lead to this gaping canyon, I guess
it's ok to be scared, just don't let that be what stops you
OK I really don't understand now!!!
these marble statues all around me
They have blindfolds, with the RLU logo on them
On stairs, in pits, on the ceiling
i, for one, am proud of you
this has very little to do with what those on the outside think of as education
once youve stopped thinking of money and structure and what people want you to say you start to realize just how much you can do
you see that door with the large black circle on it at the end?
you walk through it, you can never go back to your old life
but your purpose is for something greater
Will I ever see them again
a different you will see them
I don't know if I'm ready to be a different me
you made that choice a while ago
you always felt like you were different
and just like you know about us
we watched you grow...your grandfather’s death...
the way you never fit in...the times you did the impossible but pretended it didn’t happen
Rhys Lakes University isn’t what they think it is
now the real work can begin
